        public boolean canCastle(PieceColor color,
                boolean kingSide)

        kingSide - Indicates which side to check for castle rights.
        Returns:
        Boolean indicating whether it is possible for the input castle move.

      • gameState

        public int gameState()
        Returns the current win/loss state of the game. Impossible to tie so far. Will add functionality later.
        Returns:
        0 if tie, -1 if black win, 1 if white wins, and 2 if no win

      • generateAttackMaps

        public int[][] generateAttackMaps(PieceColor color)
        Generates a map for the input color. Each point on the map corresponds to the number of pieces of the opposite color that are threatening that point on the board. This probably should be changed to use an "Attack Map object".
        Parameters:
        color - PieceColor for the color the threats are against. Shows the threats for the opposite color.
        Returns:
        Array of threats against the input color.
